==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seminose
<hw>Sem"i*nose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>semen</ets> seed + <ets>glucose</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A carbohydrate of the glucose group found in the thickened
endosperm of certain seeds, and extracted as yellow sirup having a
sweetish-bitter taste.</def> <-- same as D-mannose; C6H12O6, a hexose
opticaly isomeric with glucose. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seminude</ent>⟦br⟧
